statement.p:
Solve each system using augmented matrix notation. Express the solution using vectors (that is, in a set-builder notation using vectors and real-variable parameters).




						\syseq{
						3x  +  6y  =  18 ; 
                   					x  +  2y  =  6  
						}





							\syseq{
							x  +  y   =  1; 
                   						x  -  y   =  -1  
							}





							\syseq{
							x_1  \+ \. +  x_3   =  4; 
                   						x_1  -  x_2  +  2x_3  =  5; 
                  						4x_1  -  x_2  +  5x_3  =  17  
							}





							\syseq{
							2a   +  b    -  c     =  2;
							2a   \+ \. +  c   =  3;
                    						a   -  b  \+ \. =  0   
							}





							\syseq{
							  x  +  2y   -   z \+ \. =  3; 
                    						2x  +  y \+ \.   w   =  4; 
                     						x  -  y    +   z   +   w   =  1  
							}





							\syseq{
							x  \+ \. +  z   +   w   =  4;
                    						2x  +  y  \+ \. -   w   =  2;
                    						3x  +  y    +   z   \+ \. =  7  
							}

ol.li:
This reduction


								\amat{
								3 6 18;
								1 2 6
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								3 6 18;
								0 0 0
								}


						leaves x leading and y free. Making y the parameter, gives x=6-2y and this solution set:
						\bigl\{\vec{6 0} + \vec{-2 1}y \mid y \text{ in }\R\bigr\}
